1-4 These will prolly be one of the most boring levels for any caster, you get a few nice spells like summon food and water and such but you already have food supplied till this level so this is the level to be kinna bored with. I suggest starting with rats and Decaying skellies till you hit level two and maybe till even level three, at level three kill beetles, spiders, and Runaways till you hit level four<BR>
<BR>
4-8 these are great levels i suggest killing kobolds for the first few levels of this and then at about level 6 i would try and find a ride or group of friends to travel to NRo the greatest newbie ground i've ever played in. At level 7 things will get kinna boring again you will have trouble soloing tough blues and so you don't gain experience all that well, this is when you group with a tank and maybe another caster (if ones available)If you're lucky enough to find a good group of people stick with them till level eight.<BR>
<BR>
8-12 Ok, at level eight head in and grab as many new spells as you can find (i suggest starting with earth pet and water pet first thenbuying the weakest of your DD spells followed by the second of you DD spells after that buy your Damage Sheilding spell as that will put alot of battle time out if you buff your pet with that.....after that go with what you think is best) Level eight is when it's time to level like a madman.....fighting yellows should give you no problem and those blues that gave you so much trouble last level will be greatly intimidated by the LOOK of your pet nor the less his power you'll hit level nine really fast if you play right and then at level nine try the same patter taking out as many yellow scarabs as you can find......i stick with the scarab pattern till about level 11 then group in the oasis against crocs.<BR>
<BR>
12-16 These levels are'nt all that exciting well at level twelve you won't get much more than a new pet which granted will help alot however, tends to be kinna dissapointing. through these levels it will appear to be alot slower because you won't do much more damage than before youre pet can just tank longer...... at level 16 you get NICE spells you do around 90 damage and your pets ROCK this level is very much like the eigth level however, i've managed to kill reds which i must say were very nice exp.<BR>
<BR>
This is about all the information i have for now but hope you learned a lil with what i posted )
