	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Re:  the post above asking about duds for gnome caster - <BR>
<BR>
As you'll discover pure casters like wiz, ench, mage, necro cannot wear armor like chain mail, or anymail for that matter.  Our duds are the robes of Norrath, ranging from newbie robes in guilds to the awesome stat-buffing robes of many of the dungeons. <BR>
<BR>
Best bet at lower levels is to save your cash, then make your way to a place like Greater Faydark where items are auctioned constantly.  Look for a damask or gossimer robe for 40-60 pp (gossimer is nice 'cuz its white).  After that comes flowing black robe (from Najena dungeon) which looks COOL and buffs INT a bit.  Sells lately for about 125 pp I think - used to be 300 :(<BR>
<BR>
Enjoy :)<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
