	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am a 16th circle Gnecro on Ayonae Ro.  My first char was a gnecro as well, but on my buddy's account, unfortunately.  I have a few tips for the gnew gnecro on the block - please forgive if I echo anything  =)<BR>
<BR>
1) Save those bone chips, folks!  You'll need them later of course, but they can be turned into hefty loot with some patience.  Keep a few stacks on your person, and check who's in the zone every now and again.  A high level necro will be more than happy to take some off your hands - I've recieved as much as 15pp per stack.<BR>
<BR>
2) Necros level 8+; get Ward Undead.  Hang a right outside of town, the opposite direction of the newbie crater - you'll see what looks like a dinosaur ribcage, with 4 skels posted around it.  This site is a very quick jog to the windmills (and the safety of Guard Mylz and Forpar Fizla).  After leveling to 12th here twice, I found myself in posession of 300+ chips.<BR>
<BR>
3) Give your pet a weapon!  I know it's obvious, I'm not trying to condescend, but keep both eyes peeled for skels with rusty scythes or 2 handers.  The extra help will be apparent.<BR>
<BR>
4) While you ARE disliked by many &quot;good&quot; townspeople, you aren't hated.  Lawn trash and the occasional minotaur are all you'll need to kill to get respect from the local merchants.<BR>
<BR>
5) Kobolds.  We've all killed more than one could count, and there's finally some comeuppance - in the kobold missionary.  A new creature in Steamfont, he can be found in the mino glen.  Beware, he's a 25+ Shaman.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck out there, gnomes - not that you'll need it.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
